---
import Layout from '../layouts/TamilLitLayout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Comparative Classical Literature">
  <div class="tamil-lit-wrapper">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <h1 class="hero-title"><span class="tamil-text">ஒப்பீட்டிலக்கியம்</span> Comparative Literature</h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">Tamil, Greek, Latin, and Sanskrit</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="prose">
          <p>Tamil literature stands alongside Greek, Latin, and Sanskrit as one of the great classical traditions of the ancient world. However, unlike Greek and Latin, Tamil has maintained an unbroken literary continuum into the modern era.</p>
          <p>The secular, humanistic approach of Sangam Akam and Puram poetry finds its closest parallels not in the Vedic hymns of North India, but in the lyric poetry of ancient Greece.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
